  <a name="background"></a>
  <h1>
    Background
  </h1>

  <p>
    At Grow Therapy, we recognized that the time between therapy sessions—the "intersession period"—was a critical but often overlooked opportunity to enhance patient outcomes. Traditional therapy models focused primarily on the 50-minute session, leaving patients without support, guidance, or tools to maintain progress throughout the week.
  </p>

  <p>
    Our research revealed that patients who engaged with therapeutic content between sessions showed 40% better outcomes and 25% fewer no-shows. However, existing solutions were fragmented, impersonal, and failed to integrate seamlessly with the therapeutic relationship.
  </p>

