  <a name="planning"></a>
  <h1>
    Planning
  </h1>

  <p>
    We began with extensive user research, conducting interviews with 50+ therapists and 100+ patients to understand their intersession needs, pain points, and desired outcomes. Key insights emerged around three core areas: continuity of care, skill reinforcement, and emotional support.
  </p>

  <p>
    Our research revealed that patients wanted personalized, therapist-guided content that felt like a natural extension of their sessions. Therapists needed tools to track progress, assign homework, and maintain therapeutic momentum without increasing their workload.
  </p>

  <p>
    We developed a comprehensive strategy that included:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li>Personalized content recommendation engine</li>
    <li>Progress tracking and mood monitoring</li>
    <li>Secure messaging and check-ins</li>
    <li>Skill-building exercises and worksheets</li>
    <li>Integration with existing therapeutic frameworks</li>
  </ul>

  <a name="designing"></a>
  <h1>
    Designing
  </h1>

  <p>
    Our design approach centered on creating a seamless, non-intrusive experience that felt like a natural extension of therapy rather than a separate app. We focused on three key design principles:
  </p>

  <h3>1. Therapeutic Continuity</h3>
  <p>
    We designed the interface to maintain the same tone, language, and visual identity as the therapy session experience. This included using familiar therapeutic terminology, maintaining the same color palette, and ensuring the content felt like it came directly from the patient's therapist.
  </p>

  <h3>2. Gentle Engagement</h3>
  <p>
    Understanding that patients might be dealing with mental health challenges, we designed interactions that were encouraging but never pushy. We implemented smart timing algorithms that suggested activities when patients were most likely to engage, and provided multiple ways to interact with content based on their current energy levels.
  </p>

  <h3>3. Progress Visualization</h3>
  <p>
    We created intuitive progress tracking that showed patients their growth over time without overwhelming them with data. This included mood charts, skill development timelines, and milestone celebrations that reinforced positive behaviors and therapeutic progress.
  </p>

  <p>
    The core experience centered around a personalized dashboard that adapted to each patient's therapeutic goals, progress, and preferences. We implemented machine learning algorithms that learned from patient behavior to suggest increasingly relevant content and activities.
  </p>
